cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a method based on deep convolutional neural networks for segmenting catheter and guidewire in 2D X-ray fluoroscopic sequences. This involves automated analysis of X-ray images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed method has applications in robotics (cs.RO) for improving guidance during interventions.
